# SwiftFormat configuration for pasta.
# Run locally: `make format` (apply) or `make format-check` (verify).
# Requires `brew install swiftformat`.
#
# Philosophy: enforce the rules that prevent real inconsistency — indentation,
# trailing whitespace, brace (K&R) style, blank-line hygiene, operator/paren spacing,
# duplicate imports — and *preserve* the author's subjective layout choices
# (single-line property/function bodies, explicit `return`, explicit type
# annotations on token tables, import order, argument wrapping, trailing commas).
# This keeps the design-system token files and compact SwiftUI views readable, and
# is an intentional, documented house style rather than the stock defaults.

--swiftversion 5.9
--indent 4

# Preserve author layout for these (don't reflow what we can't usefully auto-improve).
--funcattributes preserve
--typeattributes preserve
--wraparguments preserve
--wrapparameters preserve
--wrapcollections preserve
--marktypes never

# Relaxed subjective-layout rules (see philosophy above).
--disable redundantReturn
--disable redundantType
--disable redundantSelf
--disable redundantNilInit
--disable wrapPropertyBodies
--disable wrapFunctionBodies
--disable blankLinesBetweenScopes
--disable numberFormatting
--disable docComments
--disable redundantViewBuilder
--disable consecutiveSpaces
--disable sortImports
--disable trailingCommas
--disable wrap
--disable wrapMultilineStatementBraces

# Excludes (third-party reference + generated output).
--exclude .build,DerivedData,design,Pods
